<br>
Is anyone here still friendly with Lachadan? If so, you may wish to discuss with him his... well, rather pigheaded attitude toward employing copyright violation in the front page of Dark Legion's Web site. It seems one of his guildies &quot;borrowed&quot; someone else's commissioned EQ artwork, slapped some text over it, put a barcode over the original artist's signature, turned it into a DL magazine-style cover and claimed it as his own -- a piece which Lach then put up on their front page.<br>
<br>
They were informed rather politely about the copyright violation, and the offender took the image down from their EZBoard after several additional requests and a rather surly admission of guilt, but it remains on their front page, along with, on their boards, a lot of very... rude and unfriendly (and uninformed) response from the various members over there who seem to feel that they can break the law and not worry about harming either the original artist or their own reputations (or any more serious consequences).<br>
<br>
Here's the thread for those who want to look: <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://pub116.ezboard.com/fthedarklegion37419frm1.showMessage?topicID=1274.topic">pub116.ezboard.com/ftheda...1274.topic</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
The image is still up on their front page at <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.eq-darklegion.com">www.eq-darklegion.com</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
Again, I'm trying to reach out here, in hopes that he'll see reason and take the butchered image down before the artist's lawyers have to get involved and ISPs pull hosting and such (which they will, as soon as they're notified, if this follows most cases like this).<br>
<br>
I know a lot of people think that it's OK to take an image you see on the Web and do whatever you want to it. But the fact is that if you do that without the artist's permission -- particularly if you upload it anywhere, or put your name on it -- you've broken the law and can get seriously sued. Your desktop wallpapers probably won't get you in trouble, and most artists and photographers will never see an EQ signature file, but altering an EQ artwork and then posting it to an EQ bulletin board was probably not the best thing to do. They've been caught, but still refuse to do what they're legally required to do. I'd hate to see this turn into a real-world lawsuit, and I'd hate to have them without a host just because they won't see reason on this matter. So, if you do know Lachadan and are friendly enough with him to get him to see reason, please see if you can't do so.<br>
<br>
